content.detailedDescription: Heading east on a side street connecting with watson road on my way home from work. listening to music, i approached the stop sign across from adams furnace on watson. there's an auto shop to my right and an out of business peruvian stone shop to my left. approximately 11:40-11:45 pm. as i was about to turn right onto watson heading south, i looked up, not sure if the light caught my attention. it was slow moving for like a second or 2. i thought it was a plane or jet but it wasn't shaped like anything i've ever seen and the color of the light was so unusual and so pretty. it was like a greenish neon blue but dull and bright at the same time. there were maybe 2 lights on the craft. the color of the craft was a light and dark grey. it seemed to be flying too low to be an aircraft and heading in the opposite direction of lambert airport. it sped up so quickly and just disappeared completely out of site. i have never seen anything like this in my life but am so in awe of what i just saw. i know st. louis is close to belleville, il where scott air force base is located, and could have been a jet or whatever, but it was shaped like nothing i've ever seen and the color of those lights was so intense and how it moved. it was so graceful. just thought i'd put this info out there as i am baffled and curious more than ever. appreciate your time reading this. thank you.
content.summary: Bullet shape, big green lights maybe 1 or 2, lower than a plane flies, moving slow then super fast and just vanished .

content.detailedDescription: I was watching tv and when the show was over, i decided to take my dogs outside to go to potty. i look up at the stars on a clear night (no moon i believe) about 30 degrees fahrenheit. i notice saturn and think about taking my telescope out to see it in detail. i turn my patio light off so i can see the stars better and i look back up. i first thought i saw a shooting star but upon closer inspection i realized it was four dim whitish yellow lights in a "v" shaped formation, moving very quickly from the east. there was absolutely no audible sound. once i realized that is was a ufo it was about 90 degrees from the horizon, or right above me somewhat towards the south. i could distinctly tell the lights were not fixed. i could see the spaces between the lights growing and shrinking as they sped across the sky. overall the group moved in a straight line, east to west. from the center of the sky to fading away above the horizon in the west in 4-5 seconds. far faster than any satellite that i have ever seen. the whole encounter was around 7-8 seconds. the group of lights was about the diameter of a quarter held at arms length. i was absolutely awestruck. after the encounter i immediately texted my mom and sister explaining what i just witnessed. i kept getting waves of goosebumps because i was so amazed. truly the craziest thing i have ever seen in my 19 years of life.
content.summary: 4 dim yellow lights in a "v" went across sky in 4-5 seconds no sound

content.detailedDescription:
I was in my partners house which is in cloneygowan (a small village in co. offaly), me and my partner were outside stargazing, the village is in the middle of nowhere so there is practically no light pollution there, you can clearly see stars, planes, planets and such and clearly distinguish between them. my partner lives in a pretty large bungalo, we were outside the front door.

my partner noticed the object and pointed it out to me, we looked at it for about 5 minutes trying to figure out if it was moving, we came to a conclusion that the object is either stationary or moving towards us at an extremely slow pace.

when i first noticed the object we thought it was a plane.

after looking at its movement (or lack of movement) for about 5 minutes we came to a conclusion it is bigger than a plane, it was stationary or moving towards us extremely slow and that it was triangular in shape if you focused on it and squinted a little, it was obvious this object is very far away from us therefore the triangular shape is not apparent at first. the object was flashing 3 different colours: red, blue and green, the pattern of them is not very apparent but i wouldn't call it random. 

i had a sudden feeling of dread, i realised this could be something important, i never thought i would see something like this in my life, i have always been open to the idea that ufos and life on other planets exist yet i treat videos and such with a rational point of view trying not to have a biased view on them. i have no doubt what i saw was not a plane / star / planet. 

i took out my iphone, which was at around 20% battery at this time and started recording a video, i tried to get the object in focus but the object is too small to be properly visible on the screen, i walk towards it and as soon as i get the object on screen, several blue lines varying in thickness appeared on the screen, about 2 seconds after this my phone turned off as if the battery ran out (iphone users should be familiar with the spinning white "buffering" or loading cirlce that appears when an iphone switches off).

we ran inside the house and i immediately plugged my iphone into my laptop, i know that when my phone is out of battery and gets plugged into a charger, there appears an empty battery on the screen showing that the battery is not charged enough for the phone to turn on, this usually lasts for 7 minutes before the apple logo appears (my phone is very slow as it is the iphone 4. i have recorded many videos with my phone, the last one before my recording of the object was 2 weeks ago, there have never been problems with the video before), this time my phone showed the apple logo instantly after being plugged in and it took only around 30 seconds for the phone to turn on. the battery was 14% exactly. i copied the video onto my desktop and watched it, the blue lines appear in the video and the audio cuts off as soon as they appear. the video is attached in this report.

this experience terrified me, i have heard of ufos being able to interfere with electronics and emit electromagnetic waves, i instantly panicked as i felt i could be in danger. maybe it knows i was watching? so many thoughts rushed into my head.

after running back into the house, we tried to calm down a little by trying to figure out what this object could have been. my partner has had a fear of aliens, ufos and abductions since a very young age so i was trying to make sure they do not have a panic attack. we decided that going outside to check again was the only way to really know what this was, we grabbed binoculars and prepared to go investigate, i started recording again yet this video has my partner in it and she does not wish to be shown. the video does not contain any real evidence in my opinion, the object is not visible it is only me explaining what just happened.

we stepped outside and stood there watching for around 10 minutes, we heard a shriek which reminded me of a monkey or some kind of bird, immediately after this noise we heard something which sounded like a dog being killed or severely injured, it was a mix of a whine and a sort of scream almost, this noise terrified me and i said to my partner "lets go back inside" trying not to scare them. this experience is haunting and terrifying to recall, the emotions i experienced during this made me feel like i was in danger. i did not tick the "animal mutilation" tag on this as to not be misleading, i can only assume the strange noise was an animal being mutilated, but i really do not know as i did not see anything happen.

i do not know exactly the altitude of the object or anything like that, it was too far away. the best description of its altitude would be that of a plane.

i am attaching the video which features the interference and the object.
content.summary: Very far away blinking light traingle, affected video and cellphone, animal screams heard soon after

the next night around the same time. something else happen but it was not in the sky. i was in my bed trying to sleep but couldnt my mind started to race really fast and hurting. then it felt like the hallway started to get warm and very warm and my body couldnt move, i couldnt moved my head and then i could hear a voice say come here come here. after hearing the voice the warm went away and i could move again.

from then after those two nights i have had bad dreams very bad sometime waking up freaking out, sweating, or couldnt move feeling. my mind has race every since then. and i dont think thats the first time i have had a alien existence. i had one when i was 17.

content.detailedDescription:
I was heading north east on county road f towards hwy 65 in dresser wisconsin about 3 miles from trollhaugen ski resort. there is sort of a magical presents in a specific area of  road.  i've even stopped to take pictures in the past (i almost felt i had to) of the landscape and in the photos you can see white balls of light.  also, about a half mile before the sighting is land for sale.  another weird place that gives off a strange energy i cannot quite describe.  i'm drawn to these places, very nervous about them, and also at peace about them.  it was around 9pm towards the end of summer.  i had just gotten off of work and was heading out to pick up my children from my parents home.  i had never before seen lights, crafts, or anything strange before this.  but i have always dedicated enormous amounts of time into learning about strange phenomena, the unknown, just anything beyond our daily tunnel vision...They say you'll know what matters most to you if you pay attention to where your mind wonders...My mind is always focused on the universe and the mysteries it holds.  with that being said i'm no fool to reality.  also, i live right next to a small local airport, it's quite literally in my back yard.  i see and hear all sorts of aircraft everyday, all day.  the sighting was about 10 miles away from my home and the airport. 

as i was coming up a small hill on county road f i noticed a big orange ball shape about 300 ft above the tree line to the right of my car.  i was alone, the sun was under the horizon at this point.  i was instantly scared and started to shake.  something kept telling me "don't look, don't look!"  loud as day i could and still can hear those words.  i tried so hard not to look.  as i drove closer to where it was...I looked.  the very instant i looked directly at the orange ball the lights split, and now there were three of the same size glowing orange lights.  all within the same distance from each other, the same size, and silent.(i had turned my radio down as i was coming up the hill when i first noticed the first orange ball of light.)  it was as if it was waiting to see if i would look or not.  it was at that exact moment i almost froze and said out loud, "i should not have looked!"  i watched in my review mirror as i drove past the lights still scared...I honestly could not believe what happened...I picked up my children about 5 miles more away from the sighting and decided if the lights were still there i would take a picture on my way back.  all that was left was a tiny red light in the distance moving slowly away, not blinking, silent, no physical structure could be made out.  i stopped the car, rolled down my window and tried to take a picture of the red light but it was not showing up.  just blackness on my camera. 

to this day i am still so confused on what that was, and the fact it was at a place i had longed felt strange about.  i'm nervous to ever see something like that again...And i wonder if i wasn't suppose to look for a reason, maybe i was being protected, but since i did look...Now what? 
i included a picture i had stopped to take a couple of years before in the same area i had seen the orange lights. weird.
content.summary: Ball of orange light splits into three right in front of my face

content.detailedDescription:
Saturday evening between 11pm and midnight my wife stepped outside to let our dogs out when she noticed a really bright light flash all of a sudden in the northern sky.She looked in that direction for a few seconds when again she saw a flash of light, as if someone was turning on a spot light in the sky. she called me outside (i was in the kitchen preparing myself a snack), and when i went outside that and pointed in the direction where she last saw the flash of light, i saw it. from there we both observed this very faint object in the sky move very slowly with it flashing this spot light every so often. there wasn't a set number of seconds between flashes, it happened randomly. i called my son outside so he can also see it, which he did. it did this for around 3 to 4 minutes before it moved in an easterly direction appearing to be a very faint star. lost track of the object as it became way too faint to observe.
this is not the first time we have witnessed peculiar objects and lights in the sky. many other times we have seen orange football shaped objects hovering behind our woods (july 4th, 2011 to be exact), we have seen glowing orbs floating in the sky, military jets appearing to attempt to intercept some objects, and many other  anomalies that we simply cannot explain. i myself have also witnessed incredible sized (best way to describe it) ship silently going over me with about 50 smaller objects appearing shortly after doing what appeared to be aerobatics. not sure how this makes me feel. part of me is pretty excited and another part of me concerned.... not knowing what these things are is what causes my fear, i believe...
content.summary: Faint star like object with slow movement would turn on what appear to be spotlights

content.detailedDescription: My fiancé and i were traveling s on i95 between the fl/ga border when we witnessed a small, bright, pulsing spherical light, white/yellow in color, very high in the sky. the light remained stationary and then flew upwards at an extremely accelerated rate.  at this time we noticed several other lights moving in various formations. some of the lights moved horizontally, while others moved vertically. many of the lights changed directions over the course of 15 minutes. most of the lights remained visible in the sky for 10 minutes, moving in various directions at various speeds until they quickly accelerated vertically and disappeared. total, there were around 8-10 lights. the event ended when two planes appeared in the sky and headed towards two remaining lights. at this time, the two lights converged into one and disappeared.  i grew up near cecil field (yellowater) and an outlying naval field, so i am used to seeing strange aerial phenomenon. however, i have never seen craft move with this much variance in speed and direction.

content.detailedDescription:
Place of sighting:
- kyalami, midrand (johannesburg south africa)

time and date:
- 21:29 cat (jhb); 27 march 2016

initial siting direction:
- west west south (towards krugersdorp)

event details:
just before going to bed, i went outside onto the patio leading from our bedroom. being a clear cool autumn night, i went outside to look at the constellation of orion (westerly direction at around 30 degrees elevation at the time) to see how clear it would be. i noticed a small commercial aircraft making its way towards lanseria airport (north westerly direction from our house).

i then looked more to the south to look in the direction of where a neighbours dog was barking and noticed a string of faint coppery orange orbs in the west. these were moving in a boomerang / "loose string of pearls" formation towards pretoria (to the north west). i estimate they would have been directly overhead for the residents of krugersdorp. at the beginning of the sighting i estimate the length of the edge of this formation was about the same as holding a 4-inch long object out at an arms length

the easterly edge of the boomerang immediately reminded me of the so-called "phoenix lights" - this was the first thing which went through my head when i saw them - this because the "string" looked straight and level relative to the horizon and looked like a picture i had once seen of that phenomena (note: these objects in this sighting were much closer to one another and there were many more). this was the closest the formation was to me, thereafter it became smaller as it moved north easterly towards pretoria.

the "string" on the westerly side moved erratically, many simultaneously moving rapidly and overtaking one another, then dropping back. the same movement happened on the easterly side of the formation but not to the same extent. the shape remained a "v" regardless of the movements of the individual objects. the formation was moving between orion and sirius. 

the closest comparable motion i can think of is a flock of birds flying in a v-formation in very turbulent weather and then the speed of the movements similar to footage of the same speeded up considerably. the changing of relative positions was almost "playful" but always kept the same distance between the individual objects. 

as they moved over, the v-shape became more pronounced and less "flat" - i could not count them properly but i estimate there were over 20 individual objects, those on the easterly side being marginally brighter than those in the west). these were individual objects and not part of a single larger object.

the colour was slightly darker than the orange of the star betelgeuse, and luminosity around 20% of that star on the night

i called my wife to see the formation, but by the time she was outside, the formation was much fainter than when i had first seen it and was just about to disappear behind the tops of the trees in the north west. at this time the easterly side of the formation went straight again but the westerly side continued to move erratically. she witnessed a shooting star off to the side of where the formation was. 

during this time - of only around 10 to 15 seconds at most - i only took my eyes off the formation once when i tried to see if my wife was looking in the right direction. 

in relation to the airplane mentioned earlier, the formation was moving much faster and seemed much higher in the sky. to put the speed in perspective, the sighting covered about 3/4 of the sky and was over in the time mentioned earlier. this reminded me of the speed of a low flying fighter jet. there was no sound from the formation, and i did not hear engine noise from the airplane either. by the end of the sighting the airplane had disappeared but admittedly was not the focus of my attention. 

i expect the only reason why the objects were even visible was because of the position and luminosity of the rising moon - reflecting off the lower surfaces of the objects - much as the sun does off satellites in the early evening. they did not emit any light themselves - ruling out the typical chinese lantern misidentification. i immediately sketched the sky and the path / formation on my smartphone (attached).

i am familiar with aircraft (as we have multiple airport in the vicinity) and have been interested in aircraft since an early age. these objects and their speed, proximity to one another and movements do not fit any aircraft i am aware of. their movements would have been extremely risky - if impossible - for any formation of aircraft to attempt without colliding. the acceleration and deceleration of the objects also did not seem physically possible for a object with any weight. 

i hope this will support any other similar sightings of the 27 march 2016.

please do not hesitate to contact me for additional detail and i will supply where i am able to.
content.summary: 20 - 30 orbs in boomerang formation heading north west towards pretoria south africa

content.detailedDescription:
I was on my patio viewing the stars with google star map. i saw a flash and turned to see what it was. it was a clear night. the object appeared to be as high as the international space station (iss) when it flies over our home. the lights were sequential and in this order:

flash (white) then go black for 2-3 seconds.
soft glow (red) then go black for 2-3 seconds.
bright light (white) then go black for 3-5 seconds.

the object did not follow a straight path, but dipped up and down. we could not tell when it changed directions as it did so while all of the lights were out. 

we felt a great deal of anxiety while watching, i believe we have been nervous, irritable and anxious ever since. we stopped watching and when inside as we began to feel fear. 

we are filmmakers, photographers, stargazers and backyard astronomers. we know the airline flight paths and have watched the iss flyover many times. we also know that planes and helicopters do not go completely black and this object was way above the normal altitude, again at first i thought it was the iss.
content.summary: Unexplainable lights over south san jose

content.detailedDescription: My friend and i had gone to the maxwell wildlife preserve north of canton, ks to see their buffalo herd. as we rode around the site in an open trailer observing buffalo, i took a number of pictures with my nikon d40 digital camera (iso 200). on a whim, i took one of the sky because i liked the clouds. in the center of the sky picture (attached) is an opaque object that appears to be partially shaded from the sun, which was at about 2 o'clock outside the camera's view range. the object was not visible to the naked eye. i'm a mufon field investigator (#19371) so i submitted it to dr. bruce maccabee, photo analyst for mufon, and requested his analysis. in response, he wrote, "looks as if it might be an opaque object with a glint (reflection) from the right side. difference in brightness of the glint as compared to the dark (not illuminated by the sun) left side seems too great to be a reflection from a bird. unfortunately, the image is too "diffuse" to get an idea of the exact shape. can't do much with "surprise" image reports such as this because no info on flight dynamics. may be worth a report anyway on the off chance that someone else might have seen it and filed a report."
content.summary: An opaque object, invisible to the naked eye, in a photo taken at the maxwell wildlife preserve.
